LOCALITY UNKNOWN: 2 shells ( SMF 150087); 2 shells (labelled as
anguina
) ( NHMUK ).

MEASUREMENTS (in mm). D = 17.7–31.3, H = 7–9.1 (smallest and largest specimens found in the NHM); D = 26.2–28.8, H = 8.6–9.1 (
repercussa
, NHMUK paralectotypes ); D = 23.8, H = 8.1 ( holotype of
achatina var. castanea
); D = 17.7, H = 7 ( holotype of
achatina var. venusta
); D = 27.3, H = 8.8 ( holotype of
achatina var. repercussoides
); D = 21.8, H = 8.6 ( holotype of
achatina var. infrafasciata
); D = 19.3, H = 7.5 ( holotype of
achatina var. obesa
). Stoliczka (1871) mentioned that the largest shell was 35 mm in width.

One sample (“Attaram-Tal”, coll. Möllendorff, SMF 150092) had three shells with a somewhat elevated spire and a slightly keeled body whorl (similar to that of 

Plectopylis anguina

). This sample might be a locally isolated form with peculiar shell characters.
